  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Environmental hazards and other effects, including starvation and the long-term effects of freezing or scorching temperatures, can lead to a special condition called Exhaustion. Exhaustion is measured in six levels, each of which has a cumulative effect. Whenever a character becomes exhausted, they gain one level of Exhaustion. Finishing a long rest reduces Exhaustion by one level provided that food and drink are available.</p>",
